 series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Sulyard was born in 1376, in Eye, Suffolk, England, his father, John Sulyard, was 24 and his mother, Dorothy Bacon, was 22. He had at least 1 son with Joane Goade."},"et":{"1376–":"1376–Surnud","1376–Male":"1376–Surnud","1378–1400":"1378–1400","1400–1468":"1400–1468","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1354–1381":"1354–1381","1468":"1468","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","Eye, Mid Suffolk District, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, England","Eye, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1376–":"1376–Kuollut","1376–Male":"1376–Kuollut","1378–1400":"1378–1400","1400–1468":"1400–1468","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1354–1381":"1354–1381","1468":"1468","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","Eye, Mid Suffolk District, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, England","Eye, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1376–":"1376–Décédé","1376–Male":"1376–Décédé","1378–1400":"1378–1400","1400–1468":"1400–1468","1352–1381":"1352–1381","1354–1381":"1354–1381","1468":"1468","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","Eye, Mid Suffolk District, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, Angleterre","Eye, Suffolk, England":"Eye, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Sulyard est né en 1376, à Eye, Suffolk, Angleterre, son père, John Sulyard, avait 24 ans et sa mère, Dorothy Bacon, avait 22 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joane Goade."},"de